headline : The musician recording on the world's biggest piano
text : \r\nBack in 1987, piano maker David Klavins introduced the world's largest upright piano, which is two floors high. German musician Nils Frahm has now recorded an album on it, and the proceeds will help finance Klavins' latest project: building an even bigger piano.\r\n
